<h2>About</h2>

<h3>Portfolio Project</h3>
<p>
    Jurassic Bark is the result of my final project with the Centriq Training's Full-Stack Web Developer Program. I was tasked with creating an online reservation system, with the following requirements:
    <ul>
        <li class = "list-group-item">Pet owners can register themselves, their pets, and create reservations.
        <ul>
            <li class = "list-group-item">Add/edit pet photos and notes.</li>
            <li class = "list-group-item">View profiles and reservations for their pets.</li>
        </ul>
        </li>
        <li class = "list-group-item">
            Administrators have full CRUD functionality for Resort Locations, Reservations, and Pets.
            <ul>
                <li class = "list-group-item">
                    Administrators can limit reservations
                </li>
                <li class = "list-group-item">
                    Administrators can override the location limits
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li class = "list-group-item">
            Employees can view all reservations and pet notes.
            <ul>
                <li class = "list-group-item">
                    Employees can add and update pet notes
                </li>
                <li class = "list-group-item">
                    Employees can edit their profile details (address/telephone)
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
</p>
